Install Process / Installation

Explain the steps required to install the Rust toolchain on your system.

Verify your Rust version from the command line.

Initialize a new project with cargo and describe the generated files.

Show how to build and run a Rust program from the terminal.

Demonstrate updating Rust to the latest version.

Set the default toolchain to nightly and revert back to stable.

Compile a single .rs file without using Cargo.

Add a new dependency to Cargo.toml and build.

Explain what cargo check does compared to cargo build.

Describe the purpose of rustup versus cargo
